Random data generator

Source: R/generators.R
generator_dummy.Rd

Creates a random input/target list once and repeatedly returns list.

generator_dummy(model, batch_size)

Arguments

model

A keras model.

batch_size

Number of samples in one batch.

Examples

model <- create_model_lstm_cnn(
  maxlen = 10,
  layer_lstm = c(4),
  layer_dense = c(5))
#> Model: "model_9"
#> ________________________________________________________________________________
#>  Layer (type)                       Output Shape                    Param #     
#> ================================================================================
#>  input_10 (InputLayer)              [(None, 10, 4)]                 0           
#>  lstm_11 (LSTM)                     (None, 4)                       144         
#>  dense_13 (Dense)                   (None, 5)                       25          
#> ================================================================================
#> Total params: 169
#> Trainable params: 169
#> Non-trainable params: 0
#> ________________________________________________________________________________
gen <- generator_dummy(model, 12)
z <- gen()
x <- z[[1]]
y <- z[[2]]
dim(x)
#> [1] 12 10  4
dim(y)
#> [1] 12  5
